Reading Directories
Instructions

1) Open a directory on your computer e.g. Documents.
2) List all the contents in the directory.
3) Show all hidden folders and files.
4) Get details of all files and folders using a command shortcut.
5) What command shortcut did you use to see all the details? Write your answer below.

1) cd "directoryname"
2) ls "directoryname"
3) ls -a "directoryname"
4) ls -al "directoryname"
5) ll "directoryname"
